                                                       Chapter 1
                                                INTRODUCTION

        Dear readers,

          Stalking is not a profession, it is a way of life. This is a world where every step can be decisive, and every decision is a matter of life and death. In the grim expanses of the Zone, you can find everything: friends and enemies, wealth and poverty, secrets and dangers.

          This book is not just a reference guide, it is a set of rules and instructions that will help you survive in this dangerous world. Here you will find not only survival tips, but also stories about what awaits you in the most remote corners of the Zone, about the secrets it holds, and what trials you will have to endure.

        Strength in knowledge, strength in weapons, strength in you, Stalker!

        With respect, Nikolai Khurmenko and the IC News office
        ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                   Chapter 2
                                               Stash and Purgatory
          Purgatory - this is where your journey always begins. You have two paths: go to the village or to the lobby. To get to the village, you need to enter the right passage (with the stalker patch). Go through it and you're in the village. 
          Below will be the passage to the lobby, on the left will be the passage to the "shop", there will be a stash, on the right there is a passage to the "hospital". From the hospital you need to exit and go up until you reach the pedestrian crossing (the one with two stripes), then turn right and go up - on the left there will be a shop and on the right a passage to the stash. 
          The last passage remaining, the one in the middle called "station". There you need to exit the station and run right along the road. Then find the hospital and go up from it to the first pedestrian crossing. Then turn right and go up.
          
          So, you have arrived in the city of Chernobyl-4. And here the question arises: "What should I do now?"
          First, I suggest you familiarize yourself with your place of residence - the Stash. 
          The stash has everything you need for life. A bathroom, a bedroom, and most importantly - a blue vending machine.
          It is the only one that will keep your things safe and sound. But with a small caveat. You can't just shove things into it. There is an "E" button on the machine that you need to press, and then you can store things.

          The bathroom has a sink, but it's empty (thanks to the mayor). And the most important invention of humanity - the toilet. Well, in the bedroom, you can get a good rest.
