                                                  Chapter 5
                                                    The Zone

          The Zone is a place that has been attracting adventurers from all over the world for several decades! When people come here, they rarely think about the dangers they will encounter. Many people have perished on its wastelands from anomalies and local fauna. And why? Because they went into the Zone without thinking about their equipment. We want to fix that. 
          Here are some tips to avoid dying in the Zone:

        1. If possible, travel in a group. You might handle one or two blind dogs, but what if there are 3 or 4? Until you gain experience, you should travel in a group so others can back you up.

        2. You should always have bolts! An anomaly can be anywhere. They make sounds, but that doesn't guarantee 100% detection of an anomaly. 

        3. A radiation dosimeter should be in your pocket. There are places where radiation exceeds 4 Sv! Without a dosimeter, you might not even notice you've entered a radiation hotspot.

        4. For mutants, a shotgun and a full bandolier of buckshot works best. But there are scarier mutants, and to kill them, you'll need an assault rifle with good ammo. They inhabit the northern Zone, so at the Cordon or swamps they won't threaten you.

        5. You must have a knife! How else will you fend off bushes or cut mutant trophies? Only with a knife!

        6. Medicine. Medicine should always be on hand.
        A bandage, 2 bruise kits, a dexaline tablet. A bit more expensive would be an AI-2 and military medkits. 

        7. You shouldn't go into the Zone carelessly. First, it would be good to have a Zarya suit and an SSH-68. If you're going for artifacts, then an SSP Ecologist or Seva, definitely with a gas mask. And don't forget a detector, otherwise how are you going to catch those artifacts? 
        Well, if you're going into a firefight, then you can't do without body armor and a helmet. And in that case, it's better to take T2-T3 ammo.

